way to manipulate without generating metadata, but I need to be careful with uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring options for handling `msgs`**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking into whether I can set `msgs` to null using `org.graalvm.nativeimage.hosted.RuntimeReflection`, but that doesn’t seem feasible. Using `ResourceBundle.clearCache` along with `SoftReference` for `msgs` doesn't look like a solid plan either. I can’t find a method to invalidate `msgs`, either. I see that high coverage might be more important than a reflection reset, but I need to stay within the developer's guidelines of avoiding direct reflection. I'm considering alternatives like `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn`, but I'm unsure if Native Image needs metadata for that. It could get complicated.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering alternatives with `Unsafe`**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about using `jdk.internal.misc.Unsafe` alongside staticFieldBase and Offset from Field, but that still involves reflection, which might be problematic. I wonder if hardcoding the offset would be an option, but that seems impossible. I also thought about controlling the order of operations to trigger a class initialization failure, but that doesn’t seem viable either. It seems I need to explore other avenues to solve this without relying on those methods.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering ResourceBundle Cache**\\\\n\\\\nI'm examining if we really need `ResourceBundle.clearCache()`. Resetting the field seems sufficient, but if the locale changes, the cache could still return the previous locale. Having Locale.ROOT is fine, but should I clear it before each use? It looks like ResourceBundle caches by locale, so using clearCache might be the way to go. \\\\n\\\\nI'm also thinking about reflection to reset the messages bundle and whether to import Compatibility directly or use SWT publicly. Plus, I'm unsure about native image handling with private static fields. Responsibility for potential imports or checkstyle issues is on my mind as well.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_dGdwizzLYaYUmPqZaH91SBwS|fc_03e72d197ecc5dca016a1ea01b5e108197b08c8e766a1e7660\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/3.133.0/src/test/java/org_eclipse_platform/org_eclipse_swt_win32_win32_x86_64/CompatibilityTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_eclipse_platform.org_eclipse_swt_win32_win32_x86_64;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\\nimport java.util.Locale;\\nimport java.util.ResourceBundle;\\n\\nimport org.eclipse.swt.SWT;\\nimport org.eclipse.swt.internal.Compatibility;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class CompatibilityTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void getMessageLoadsResourceBundleForPlainAndFormattedMessages() throws Exception {\\n        Locale previousLocalread from environment variable: GRAALVM_HOME\\n[native-image-plugin] Native Image executable path: /home/mihailo/.sdkman/candidates/java/25.0.2-graal/lib/svm/bin/native-image\\nApply file:///home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata-copy/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/7707-f988d6cb/tests/src/org.eclipse.platform/org.eclipse.swt.win32.win32.x86_64/3.133.0/build/resources/test/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json\\nApply jar:file:///home/mihailo/.sdkman/candidates/java/25.0.2-graal/lib/svm/library-support.jar!/META-INF/native-image/com.oracle.svm/thirdparty/native-image.properties\\nApply jar:file:///home/mihailo/.sdkman/candidates/java/25.0.2-graal/lib/svm/library-support.jar!/META-INF/native-image/com.oracle.svm/polyglo